pages.title: Kelenken
pages.text: The genus name references a spirit in Tehuelche mythology, and the specific name honors the discoverer.$(br2)The holotype consists of one of the most complete skulls known of a large phorusrhacid, as well as a tarsometatarsus lower leg bone and a phalanx toe bone.
